---
/**
 * Animated cache line fetch: shows CPU requesting a[0] and getting a 64-byte
 * cache line (16 floats) loaded from RAM into L1.
 */
---

<figure class="cacheline-anim">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 700 235" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Cache line animation: CPU fetches 64 bytes (16 floats) from RAM">
    <!-- RAM array -->
    <text x="280" y="20" class="title">RAM, array a[]</text>
    {Array.from({ length: 16 }).map((_, i) => (
      <g class="ram-cell" style={`animation-delay: ${0.8 + i * 0.05}s`}>
        <rect x={20 + i * 33} y="30" width="31" height="28" rx="3"
              class={i < 16 ? "cell fetched" : "cell"} />
        <text x={35.5 + i * 33} y="49" class="cell-text">{`a[${i}]`}</text>
      </g>
    ))}
    <rect x="18" y="28" width={16 * 33 + 2} height="32" rx="4" class="cacheline-highlight" />
    <text x={20 + 16 * 33 / 2} y="74" class="bracket-label">64 bytes = 1 cache line = 16 floats</text>

    <!-- Arrow from RAM to cache -->
    <line x1="284" y1="82" x2="284" y2="115" class="fetch-arrow" />
    <polygon points="279,112 289,112 284,120" class="fetch-arrowhead" />

    <!-- L1 Cache -->
    <rect x="134" y="125" width="300" height="40" rx="6" class="cache-box" />
    <text x="284" y="150" class="cache-label">L1 Cache, 64-byte line</text>

    <!-- Arrow from cache to CPU -->
    <line x1="284" y1="170" x2="284" y2="192" class="fetch-arrow" />
    <polygon points="279,188 289,188 284,198" class="fetch-arrowhead" />

    <!-- CPU -->
    <rect x="224" y="200" width="120" height="28" rx="6" class="cpu-box" />
    <text x="284" y="219" class="cache-label">CPU core</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>When the CPU reads <code>a[0]</code>, it fetches an entire 64-byte cache line: <code>a[0]</code> through <code>a[15]</code>. The next 15 reads are served from L1 — no RAM access needed.</figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .cacheline-anim {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .cacheline-anim svg {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 700px;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .cacheline-anim figcaption {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #888;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .title {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #555;
  }
  .cell {
    fill: #f0f0f0;
    stroke: #ccc;
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .cell.fetched {
    fill: #dbe7fa;
    stroke: #7da4d9;
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }
  .cell-text {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #444;
  }
  .cacheline-highlight {
    fill: none;
    stroke: #4a9eff;
    stroke-width: 2;
    stroke-dasharray: 6 3;
    animation: dash-march 1s linear infinite;
  }
  .bracket-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    fill: #4a9eff;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-anchor: middle;
  }
  .fetch-arrow {
    stroke: #4a9eff;
    stroke-width: 2;
    stroke-dasharray: 200;
    stroke-dashoffset: 200;
    animation: draw-line 0.6s ease-out 0.3s forwards;
  }
  .fetch-arrowhead {
    fill: #4a9eff;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fade-in 0.3s ease-out 0.9s forwards;
  }
  .ram-cell {
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fade-in 0.3s ease-out forwards;
  }
  .cache-box {
    fill: #eef4ff;
    stroke: #9bb8e8;
    stroke-width: 1.5;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fade-in 0.4s ease-out 1.2s forwards;
  }
  .cpu-box {
    fill: #e8e8e8;
    stroke: #aaa;
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }
  .cache-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #555;
  }
  @keyframes fade-in {
    to { opacity: 1; }
  }
  @keyframes draw-line {
    to { stroke-dashoffset: 0; }
  }
  @keyframes dash-march {
    to { stroke-dashoffset: -18; }
  }
</style>
